    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>8 ounces chow mein noodles or egg noodles</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>2 cups shredded cabbage</li>
            <li>1 cup julienned carrots</li>
            <li>2 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1/4 cup soy sauce</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons oyster sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon hoisin sauce</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon sugar</li>
            <li>1/2 cup chicken broth</li>
            <li>Sliced green onions for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>main dish</li>
            <li>Asian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Cook the chow mein noodles or egg noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.</li>
            <li>In a wok or large skillet, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add sliced chicken and cook until browned and cooked through. Remove chicken from the pan and set aside.</li>
            <li>In the same pan, add more oil if needed and saut√© shredded cabbage, julienned carrots, and minced garlic until vegetables are tender-crisp.</li>
            <li>Return the cooked chicken to the pan with the vegetables.</li>
            <li>In a small bowl, whisk together soy sauce, oyster sauce, hoisin sauce, sugar, and chicken broth. Pour the sauce over the chicken and vegetables, tossing to coat evenly.</li>
            <li>Add the cooked chow mein noodles to the pan and toss everything together until well combined and heated through.</li>
            <li>Serve the Chow Mein in bowls, garnished with sliced green onions.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious homemade Chow Mein!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

